 accurately describes the one-year relative deadline for notifying the other party of a defect in consent and the legal consequence of failing to do so (ratification). Thus, the statement is **correct**.\n-   **Statement iii:** The dates 1971 (federal) and 1990 (Appenzell Innerrhoden) are historically accurate key milestones in Swiss legal history. The phrasing \"Before, women could not participate...\" contextually refers to the specific jurisdictions mentioned (federal and AI) prior to those dates. Thus, the statement is **correct**.\n\n**Eliminate Incorrect Answers**\n-   Since statements i, ii, and iii are all legally and historically correct, any option suggesting they are incorrect is wrong.\n-   Option B claims all are incorrect.\n-   Option C claims i and iii are incorrect.\n-   Option D claims iii is incorrect.\n-   Option A states that \"none of the statements\" are incorrect, which aligns with the analysis.\n\n**Conclusion**\nAll three statements provided in the question are correct representations of Swiss law and history. Therefore, none of the statements are incorrect.\n\nFinal Answer: ###A###"]
