he Specific Part. Since Art. 12 SCC is located in the General Part, this statement is **incorrect**.\n-   **Statement iii:** The timeline provided (1st century BCE to 3rd century CE) accurately reflects the classical period of Roman law from which the Digest's content was sourced. Therefore, statement iii is **correct**.\n\n**Eliminate Incorrect Answers**\nThe question asks to identify the **incorrect** statements.\n-   **A) i, ii, and iii:** Incorrect choice because statement iii is correct.\n-   **B) i and iii:** Incorrect choice because statement iii is correct.\n-   **C) ii and iii:** Incorrect choice because statement iii is correct.\n-   **D) i and ii:** Correct choice. Both statement i (regarding res judicata) and statement ii (regarding the location of the definition of intention) are incorrect.\n\n**Conclusion**\nStatements i and ii are incorrect, while statement iii is correct. Therefore, the option identifying i and ii is the right answer.\n\nFinal Answer: ###D###"]
