 Spouses**\n    *   *Rule:* Under Art. 9 of the Federal Direct Tax Act (DBG) and corresponding cantonal laws, the income and wealth of spouses who live in a legally and factually unseparated marriage are aggregated (family taxation).\n    *   *Application:* Swiss law mandates joint taxation for married couples living together. There is no right of option to choose separate taxation. Separate taxation only occurs if the spouses divorce or live separately (maintaining separate households).\n    *   *Conclusion:* Statement ii is **False**.\n\n*   **Statement iii: Taxation of Foreign Real Estate**\n    *   *Rule:* Residents in Switzerland are subject to unlimited tax liability on their worldwide income (Art. 6 para. 1 DBG). However, there is a unilateral exemption for businesses, permanent establishments, and **real estate located abroad**.\n    *   *Application:* The apartment is located in Amsterdam. Therefore, the income derived from this property is exempt from Swiss income tax.\n    *   *Note on Progression:* While the income is not *taxed* (it is excluded from the tax base), it is taken into account to determine the tax rate applicable to the remaining Swiss income (exemption with progression, Art. 7 para. 1 DBG). However, the statement \"is not taxable in Switzerland\" is legally correct because the sovereignty to tax that specific income lies with the Netherlands (situs principle), and Switzerland unilaterally exempts it.\n    *   *Conclusion:* Statement iii is **True**.\n\n**4. Eliminate Incorrect Answers**\n*   **A) ii:** Incorrect, as statement ii is false.\n*   **B) i and ii:** Incorrect, as both statements are false.\n*   **C) i, ii, and iii:** Incorrect, as i and ii are false.\n*   **D) iii:** Correct, as statement iii is the only true statement.\n\n**5. Conclusion**\nStatement i confuses vertical taxation with horizontal double taxation. Statement ii contradicts the mandatory joint taxation principle. Statement iii correctly reflects the exemption of foreign real estate income from the Swiss tax base.\n\nFinal Answer: ###D###"]
