 legislative matters. Furthermore, the statement contains a drafting error (repetition of sentences). More importantly, logical deduction from the options forces this statement to be incorrect (see below). Thus, **Statement i is incorrect**.\n-   **Statement ii**: Cantons are strictly prohibited from levying a VAT because it is an exclusive federal tax (Art. 130 and 134 Cst.). The claim that Zurich can introduce a VAT \"without any restrictions\" is blatantly false. Thus, **Statement ii is incorrect**.\n-   **Statement iii**: Commercial partnerships (specifically General and Limited Partnerships) are distinct procedural entities. If a partnership wishes to assert a right or be sued for a partnership debt, it acts (or is acted against) under its firm name (Art. 562 CO). While they lack full juridical personality, the law requires them to act in their own name in proceedings involving partnership assets. Thus, **Statement iii is correct**.\n\n**Eliminate Incorrect Answers**\n-   **Statement ii is definitely incorrect**, so the correct answer choice must include \"ii\". This eliminates choices B and D.\n-   We are left with A (i, ii, and iii) and C (i and ii).\n-   Since **Statement iii is correct**, choice A is wrong.\n-   This leaves choice C. Note that for choice C to be the answer, Statement i must be incorrect. As analyzed, Statement i is incorrect (due to the \"similar\" vs \"equal\" distinction and/or the repetition error).\n\n**Conclusion**\nStatements i and ii are incorrect. Statement iii is correct. Therefore, the choice identifying the incorrect statements is C.\n\nFinal Answer: ###C###"]
