, the specific inquiry into the *method and possibility of knowing* them is the definition of epistemology. Labeling this as ontology is incorrect. Thus, statement (iii) does not apply.\n\n**Eliminate Incorrect Answers**\n*   **A) i:** Incorrect, because statement (i) is a valid classification (descriptive).\n*   **C) i and iii:** Incorrect, because statement (i) is valid.\n*   **D) i, ii, and iii:** Incorrect, because statements (i) and (ii) are valid.\n\n**Conclusion**\nThe question asks to identify the statements that **do not apply**. Statements (i) and (ii) are correct classifications. Statement (iii) incorrectly identifies an epistemological question as ontological. Therefore, only statement (iii) does not apply.\n\nFinal Answer: ###B###"]
