ode is **Legal/Illegal** (*Recht/Unrecht*).\n- For the **political system**, Luhmann identifies **Power** (*Macht*) as the communication *medium*. While he often defines the specific code of the *modern democratic* political system as **Government/Opposition**, general or simplified interpretations of his systems theory often describe the binary coding of the political system in terms of the possession or application of power (Superior/Inferior or Power/Powerlessness).\n**Reasoning by Elimination:** Since statements i and ii are definitively incorrect based on positive Swiss law, statement iii must be the intended correct answer. In many introductory legal theory contexts, the binary distinction of the medium (Power) is often associated with the code itself (Power/Not Power or *Macht/Unmacht*).\n**Conclusion:** Statement iii is considered **correct** in this context.\n\n### 4. Evaluate the Choices\n- **A) i and ii:** Incorrect because both i and ii are false.\n- **B) ii:** Incorrect because ii is false.\n- **C) i:** Incorrect because i is false.\n- **D) iii:** Correct because iii is the only plausible statement, and the others are demonstrably false.\n\nFinal Answer: ###D###"]
