cal construction, Swiss doctrine and case law predominantly classify such expert opinions (Gutachten) as Simple Mandates.\n*   **Statement i (Revocation):** Since the contract is a Simple Mandate, Katrina has the mandatory right to revoke the contract at any time under Art. 404 CO. Thus, this statement **applies**.\n*   **Statement ii (Remuneration):** The definition of a Simple Mandate does not require remuneration. It can be free of charge. The statement claims remuneration is \"in any case compulsory,\" which is legally incorrect. Thus, this statement **does not apply**.\n*   **Statement iii (Guaranteed Result):** A valuation is an opinion based on professional expertise. The agent promises diligent conduct, not that the valuation will match a specific market price or be \"correct\" in an absolute sense. It is not an agreement on a measurable result that can be guaranteed (unlike a Werkvertrag). Thus, this statement **does not apply**.\n\n**Eliminate Incorrect Answers**\nThe question asks for statements that **do not apply**.\n*   Statement i applies (it is true).\n*   Statement ii does not apply (it is false).\n*   Statement iii does not apply (it is false).\n\nTherefore, we are looking for the combination of ii and iii.\n*   A) Includes i (which applies).\n*   B) Includes i (which applies).\n*   C) Only includes iii (misses ii).\n*   D) Includes ii and iii (both do not apply).\n\n**Conclusion**\nStatements ii and iii are legally incorrect descriptions of the situation under Swiss Law. Therefore, D is the correct choice.\n\nFinal Answer: ###D###"]
