applies as the general rule.\n\n**Analysis of Statement iii:**\n\"Swiss commercial law is based on a comprehensive codification of the civil code in the 2000s.\"\n*   **Legal Rule:** Swiss commercial law is primarily contained in the **Code of Obligations (CO/OR)** and the **Civil Code (CC/ZGB)**. Switzerland follows a monistic system (no separate commercial code).\n*   **Fact Check:** The Swiss Civil Code was enacted in **1907** (effective 1912), and the Code of Obligations in **1911** (effective 1912). There was **no** comprehensive codification of the civil code in the 2000s. While there were revisions (e.g., GmbH law in 2008, ZPO in 2011), the foundational codification dates back to the early 20th century.\n*   **Conclusion:** This statement is factually **incorrect**.\n\n**Evaluation of Choices:**\n*   Statement i is correct.\n*   Statement ii is considered incorrect (due to the denial of the abstract presumption).\n*   Statement iii is definitely incorrect.\n\nThe question asks for the incorrect statements. The combination of **ii and iii** fits this analysis.\n\nFinal Answer: ###A###"]
