as a mandate. In a mandate, the agent owes a duty of care, not a guaranteed result. Therefore, this statement is **false**.\n*   **Statement ii:** \"Katrina can revoke the contract with Dr. Genius at any time.\"\n    Because the contract is classified as a mandate, Art. 404 CO applies. This article grants both parties the mandatory right to terminate the contract at any time (subject potentially to damages if done at an inopportune time, but the right to revoke remains). Therefore, this statement is **true**.\n\n**Eliminate Incorrect Answers**\n*   **B) i:** Incorrect because statement i is false; a valuation is not a guaranteed result.\n*   **C) none of the statements:** Incorrect because statement ii is true.\n*   **D) i and ii:** Incorrect because statement i is false.\n\n**Conclusion**\nStatement ii is the only correct statement based on the classification of the agreement as a mandate.\n\nFinal Answer: ###A###"]
