ty. Before this decree, Roman legal experts (jurists) were divided on the issue (some favoring the landowner via accession, others the finder via occupatio). The rule was an imperial enactment that settled a dispute, not merely a consensus or \"opinion of the legal experts.\" Attributing the binding rule solely to the \"opinion of experts\" is historically and legally imprecise.\n*Result: Statement iii is incorrect.*\n\n**Step 4: Analyze Statement iv**\n\"The constitutional principles of administrative law set out in the Federal constitution only apply with respect to activities of the Swiss confederation. However, they do not apply vis-à-vis the cantons.\"\nThe fundamental principles of the Federal Constitution, including those governing administrative action (e.g., legality, public interest, proportionality, good faith under Art. 5 and Art. 9 BV), apply to all state activities at all levels, including the Cantons (Art. 35, Art. 49 BV).\n*Result: Statement iv is incorrect.*\n\n**Conclusion**\nAll four statements contain legal or factual errors. Therefore, none of the statements are correct.\n\nFinal Answer: ###C###"]
