aces a custodial sentence of more than one year, is in pre-trial detention for more than 10 days, or cannot safeguard their own interests due to their physical or mental condition.\n\n### Application and Reasoning\n*   **Statement i:** \"State action with only limited effects may still be suitable and proportionate.\"\n    *   According to the definition of suitability, a measure only needs to contribute to the goal. A measure with limited effectiveness is not automatically unsuitable. Furthermore, if the interference with private rights is minor, a measure with limited positive effects can still be proportionate *stricto sensu*. The use of the word \"may\" makes this statement legally **correct**.\n*   **Statement ii:** \"It is a Swiss particularity that all major political parties are represented in the Federal Council. To this effect, the so-called magic formula was established (by practice, not based on an explicit provision in the Constitution).\"\n    *   This accurately describes the Swiss system of concordance. The \"magic formula\" is indeed a political agreement/practice and is not found in the text of the Constitution. This statement is **correct**.\n*   **Statement iii:** \"In Swiss criminal proceedings, the accused person never has to be represented by defence counsel if he/she doesn’t want to.\"\n    *   This statement is contradicted by Art. 130 StPO. In cases of mandatory defense, the accused *must* be represented. If they refuse to choose a lawyer, the state will appoint an official defense counsel (*Pflichtverteidiger*) regardless of the accused's wishes. The word \"never\" makes this statement **incorrect**.\n\n### Eliminate Incorrect Answers\n*   **A) i, ii, and iii:** Incorrect because statement iii is false.\n*   **C) iii:** Incorrect because statement iii is false.\n*   **D) none of the statements:** Incorrect because statements i and ii are true.\n*   **E) I don't know:** Incorrect.\n\n### Conclusion\nStatements i and ii are correct, while statement iii is incorrect. Therefore, the correct option is B.\n\nFinal Answer: ###B###"]
