 ii:** *\"Katrina can revoke the contract with Dr. Genius at any time.\"*\n    *   **Rule:** Art. 404 para. 1 CO states: \"The agency contract may be revoked or terminated by either party at any time.\" This is a mandatory provision of Swiss law for mandates.\n    *   **Application:** As the contract is a mandate, Katrina has the mandatory right to terminate the relationship at any moment.\n    *   **Verdict:** Statement ii is **True**.\n\n*   **Analysis of Statement iii:** *\"Paying a remuneration is in any case compulsory in order for a contract to be characterised as a simple agency contract.\"*\n    *   **Rule:** Art. 394 para. 3 CO states: \"A remuneration is payable if agreed or customary.\"\n    *   **Application:** A mandate can be gratuitous (free of charge). Remuneration is not a constitutive element of the definition of a mandate (unlike an employment contract).\n    *   **Verdict:** Statement iii is **False**.\n\n*   **Analysis of Statement iv:** *\"If Katrina revokes the contract at an inopportune point in time, she must compensate Dr. Genius for any resulting damage.\"*\n    *   **Rule:** Art. 404 para. 2 CO states: \"However, if the contract is terminated at an inopportune juncture, the terminating party must compensate the other for any resultant damage.\"\n    *   **Application:** This is the specific statutory exception to the \"free termination\" rule. If the termination occurs at a time that causes unreasonable difficulty or damage to the other party (Unzeit), indemnification (negative interest) is due.\n    *   **Verdict:** Statement iv is **True**.\n\n**4. Eliminate Incorrect Answers**\n*   **A) i:** Incorrect because statement i is false.\n*   **B) i and iv:** Incorrect because statement i is false.\n*   **D) iv:** Incorrect because it is incomplete; statement ii is also true.\n\n**5. Conclusion**\nStatements **ii** and **iv** are legally correct based on the rules governing the Simple Agency Contract (Mandate) in the Swiss Code of Obligations. Therefore, choice C is the correct answer.\n\nFinal Answer: ###C###"]
