. The distinction between \"is\" and \"ought\" is crucial, and using incompatible theories is not a recommended practice. Thus, the statement is incorrect.\n2.  **Statement ii:** Carl Stooss did not advocate for *only* retributive sanctions. His major contribution was the integration of preventive measures alongside retributive punishment to address the dangerousness of offenders. Thus, the statement is incorrect.\n3.  **Statement iii:** This statement accurately reflects Art. 482 ZGB. The testator has the right to impose burdens and conditions. Specifically regarding burdens, the law grants any interested party the right to demand their execution (*Vollzug der Auflage*) once the will is effective. While conditions operate differently (suspending or resolving rights), the statement correctly describes the rule regarding the enforceability of burdens attached to a will.\n\n**Eliminate Incorrect Answers**\n-   **A) ii and iii:** Incorrect because statement ii is false.\n-   **B) ii:** Incorrect because statement ii is false.\n-   **D) none of the statements:** Incorrect because statement iii is true.\n\n**Conclusion**\nStatement iii is the only correct statement, as it aligns with the statutory provisions of the Swiss Civil Code regarding testamentary burdens. Statements i and ii are theoretically and historically inaccurate.\n\nFinal Answer: ###C###"]
