ational rules (historically), the AG generally enjoys a higher reputation and perceived trustworthiness in the Swiss business environment compared to a GmbH.\n*   **Statement iv:** Incorrect. While the *nominal* capital must be at least CHF 100,000, Madeleine only needs to provide CHF 50,000 in cash (or kind) to actually *set up* the company (partial liberation).\n\n**Eliminate Incorrect Answers**\n*   **A)** Incorrect, as statements i and iii are valid.\n*   **B)** Incorrect, as it omits statement i.\n*   **C)** Incorrect, as statements ii (wrong liability definition) and iv (wrong cash requirement) are false.\n*   **D)** Correct, as it includes the two legally accurate statements regarding the nature of the business and its reputation.\n\n**Conclusion**\nStatements i and iii are correct. Statement i accurately reflects the capitalistic nature of an AG, and statement iii reflects the common business perception. Statement ii is legally inaccurate regarding the scope of liability, and statement iv ignores the possibility of partial liberation (requiring only CHF 50,000 to start).\n\nFinal Answer: ###D###"]
