trina can revoke the contract with Dr. Genius at any time.\" This aligns with the mandatory rule of Art. 404 para. 1 CO for mandates. Thus, this statement **applies**.\n*   **Statement iii:** \"Estimating the value of a real estate is an agreement on a measurable result that can be guaranteed.\" As established, a valuation is an expert opinion, not a guaranteed objective result (unlike building a wall). The agent cannot guarantee the \"correctness\" of the value in an absolute sense, only the diligence of the method. Thus, this statement **does not apply**.\n*   **Statement iv:** \"Paying a remuneration is in any case compulsory in order for a contract to be characterised as a simple agency contract.\" Since mandates can be gratuitous (Art. 394 para. 3 CO), remuneration is not compulsory for the contract's existence. Thus, this statement **does not apply**.\n\n**Eliminate Incorrect Answers**\nThe question asks for statements that **do not apply**.\n*   A) iii: Incorrect because iv also does not apply.\n*   B) i, ii, iii, and iv: Incorrect because i and ii do apply.\n*   C) i and iv: Incorrect because i applies.\n*   D) iii and iv: Correct. Both statements are legally incorrect regarding the nature of the contract and the requirements for a mandate.\n\n**Conclusion**\nStatements iii and iv are the ones that do not apply to the legal context of a mandate for real estate valuation.\n\nFinal Answer: ###D###"]
